The paper discusses a probabilistic model for summarizing data using itemsets, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) communities. The iterative approach to finding the most interesting itemsets also involves a selection process, which is related to feature selection and dimensionality reduction, topics that are often discussed in the data science (cs.DS) community. Finally, the use of Bayesian Information Criterion suggests a focus on statistical inference and model selection, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
